text: Stavoren (formerly Staveren; ) is a city in the Dutch province of Friesland, on the coast of the IJsselmeer. Stavoren got city rights between 1060 and 1067. It is part of the municipality of Súdwest-Fryslân. In 2024, 945 people lived there. Category:Former municipalities of Friesland Category:Cities in Friesland Category:Súdwest-Fryslân
